</p>
<p id="l29">
<a title="Bold Italic" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Bold_Italic">Bold Italic</a> 
</p>
<p id="l31">
<a title="ITALIC BOLD CAPS" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/ITALIC_BOLD_CAPS">ITALIC BOLD CAPS</a> 
</p>
<p id="l33">
<a title="Italic Bold Caps & Small Caps" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Italic_Bold_Caps_%26_Small_Caps">Italic Bold Caps &amp; Small Caps</a> 
</p>
<p id="l35">
<a title="italic bold small caps" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/italic_bold_small_caps">italic bold small caps</a> 
</p>
<p id="l37">
Some writers tend to use all of these forms of emphasis, sometimes in the same paragraph. 
</p>
